    "intro": "The chapter divides naturally into five movements: flight from Jezebel (1-3), wilderness collapse and angelic provision (4-8), theophany at Horeb (9-14), recommission and remnant (15-18), and the call of Elisha (19-21). Each movement answers the question the previous one raised. Hebrew terms are transliterated when they sharpen meaning.",
